.TH SIMPLE_SHELL 1 "April 2025" "Version 1.0.0" "Simple Shell Manual"

.SH NAME
simple_shell \- A simple UNIX command interpreter.

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B simple_shell
is a simple UNIX command interpreter that mimics the behavior of the original Bourne shell (sh). It provides a basic command-line interface for users to execute commands and manage processes.

.SH USAGE
The shell can be used in two modes:
.TP
.B Interactive Mode
The shell prompts the user for input and executes commands line by line.
.TP
.B Non-Interactive Mode
The shell reads commands from a file or standard input and executes them.

.SH OPTIONS
.B script_file
Specifies a file containing commands to execute in non-interactive mode.

.SH BUILT-IN COMMANDS
The following built-in commands are supported:
.TP
.B cd
Change the current working directory.
.TP
.B exit
Exit the shell.
.TP
.B env
Display the current environment variables.

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B Interactive Mode:
.nf
$ ./hsh
$ ls
$ pwd
$ exit
.fi
.TP
.B Non-Interactive Mode:
.nf
$ echo "ls -l" | ./hsh
.fi

